            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3ECompromise%20is%20the%20price%20a%20person%20is%20willing%20to%20pay%20to%20a%20false%20god.%20That%20was%20Jehoshaphat's%20problem.%20In%20an%20effort%20to%20promote%20peace%20and%20unity%2C%20he%20was%20willing%20to%20ally%20himself%20with%20Ahab%2C%20a%20man%20who%20was%20vile%20and%20wicked%20before%20God%20(1%20Kings%2022%3A4).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPeople%20often%20compromise%20because%20of%20a%20desire%20to%20be%20socially%20accepted.%20They%20overlook%20glaring%20abuses%20of%20God's%20Word%20in%20order%20to%20maintain%20relationships.%20Micaiah%2C%20however%2C%20refused%20to%20compromise%20or%20make%20even%20one%20small%20concession%20to%20Ahab's%20false%20religious%20system.%20He%20was%20willing%20to%20endure%20physical%20attack%20and%20imprisonment%20just%20to%20maintain%20the%20witness%20of%20truth%20against%20Ahab%20(1%20Kings%2022%3A17%2C%2022-24).%20Although%20confined%20in%20prison%2C%20Micaiah%20was%20safer%20than%20was%20Jehoshaphat%2C%20who%20almost%20lost%20his%20life%20in%20the%20brief%20battle%20that%20ensued.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ELook%20at%20the%20end%20result%20of%20compromise%2C%20and%20settle%20in%20your%20mind%20that%20you%20owe%20no%20allegiance%20to%20the%20idols%20of%20this%20world.%20They%20and%20their%20worshipers%20will%20one%20day%20perish%20with%20the%20same%20fate%20as%20Ahab's!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Kings.22:1-53",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E1%20Kings%2022%3A1-53%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_1%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Kings%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJehoshaphat%20and%20Ahab%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EFor%20three%20years%20there%20was%20no%20war%20between%20Aram%20and%20Israel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_2%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20during%20the%20third%20year%2C%20King%20Jehoshaphat%20of%20Judah%20went%20to%20visit%20King%20Ahab%20of%20Israel.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_3%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EDuring%20the%20visit%2C%20the%20king%20of%20Israel%20said%20to%20his%20officials%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BDo%20you%20realize%20that%20the%20town%20of%20Ramoth-gilead%20belongs%20to%20us%3F%20And%20yet%20we%26%23x2019%3Bve%20done%20nothing%20to%20recapture%20it%20from%20the%20king%20of%20Aram!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_4%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20he%20turned%20to%20Jehoshaphat%20and%20asked%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWill%20you%20join%20me%20in%20battle%20to%20recover%20Ramoth-gilead%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EJehoshaphat%20replied%20to%20the%20king%20of%20Israel%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhy%2C%20of%20course!%20You%20and%20I%20are%20as%20one.%20My%20troops%20are%20your%20troops%2C%20and%20my%20horses%20are%20your%20horses.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_5%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Jehoshaphat%20added%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BBut%20first%20let%26%23x2019%3Bs%20find%20out%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20says.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_6%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20the%20king%20of%20Israel%20summoned%20the%20prophets%2C%20about%20400%26%23xA0%3Bof%20them%2C%20and%20asked%20them%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BShould%20I%20go%20to%20war%20against%20Ramoth-gilead%2C%20or%20should%20I%20hold%20back%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EThey%20all%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BYes%2C%20go%20right%20ahead!%20The%20Lord%20will%20give%20the%20king%20victory.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_7%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Jehoshaphat%20asked%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BIs%20there%20not%20also%20a%20prophet%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20here%3F%20We%20should%20ask%20him%20the%20same%20question.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_8%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20king%20of%20Israel%20replied%20to%20Jehoshaphat%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThere%20is%20one%20more%20man%20who%20could%20consult%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20for%20us%2C%20but%20I%20hate%20him.%20He%20never%20prophesies%20anything%20but%20trouble%20for%20me!%20His%20name%20is%20Micaiah%20son%20of%20Imlah.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EJehoshaphat%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThat%26%23x2019%3Bs%20not%20the%20way%20a%20king%20should%20talk!%20Let%26%23x2019%3Bs%20hear%20what%20he%20has%20to%20say.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_9%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20the%20king%20of%20Israel%20called%20one%20of%20his%20officials%20and%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BQuick!%20Bring%20Micaiah%20son%20of%20Imlah.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_10%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EMicaiah%20Prophesies%20against%20Ahab%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EKing%20Ahab%20of%20Israel%20and%20King%20Jehoshaphat%20of%20Judah%2C%20dressed%20in%20their%20royal%20robes%2C%20were%20sitting%20on%20thrones%20at%20the%20threshing%20floor%20near%20the%20gate%20of%20Samaria.%20All%20of%20Ahab%26%23x2019%3Bs%20prophets%20were%20prophesying%20there%20in%20front%20of%20them.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_11%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EOne%20of%20them%2C%20Zedekiah%20son%20of%20Kenaanah%2C%20made%20some%20iron%20horns%20and%20proclaimed%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20says%3A%20With%20these%20horns%20you%20will%20gore%20the%20Arameans%20to%20death!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_12%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EAll%20the%20other%20prophets%20agreed.%20%26%23x201C%3BYes%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20they%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3Bgo%20up%20to%20Ramoth-gilead%20and%20be%20victorious%2C%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20will%20give%20the%20king%20victory!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_13%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20messenger%20who%20went%20to%20get%20Micaiah%20said%20to%20him%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BLook%2C%20all%20the%20prophets%20are%20promising%20victory%20for%20the%20king.%20Be%20sure%20that%20you%20agree%20with%20them%20and%20promise%20success.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_14%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Micaiah%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BAs%20surely%20as%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20lives%2C%20I%20will%20say%20only%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20tells%20me%20to%20say.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_15%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Micaiah%20arrived%20before%20the%20king%2C%20Ahab%20asked%20him%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BMicaiah%2C%20should%20we%20go%20to%20war%20against%20Ramoth-gilead%2C%20or%20should%20we%20hold%20back%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EMicaiah%20replied%20sarcastically%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BYes%2C%20go%20up%20and%20be%20victorious%2C%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20will%20give%20the%20king%20victory!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_16%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20king%20replied%20sharply%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BHow%20many%20times%20must%20I%20demand%20that%20you%20speak%20only%20the%20truth%20to%20me%20when%20you%20speak%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_17%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Micaiah%20told%20him%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BIn%20a%20vision%20I%20saw%20all%20Israel%20scattered%20on%20the%20mountains%2C%20like%20sheep%20without%20a%20shepherd.%20And%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20said%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BTheir%20master%20has%20been%20killed.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E22%3A17%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EThese%20people%20have%20no%20master.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Send%20them%20home%20in%20peace.%26%23x2019%3B%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_18%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BDidn%26%23x2019%3Bt%20I%20tell%20you%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20the%20king%20of%20Israel%20exclaimed%20to%20Jehoshaphat.%20%26%23x201C%3BHe%20never%20prophesies%20anything%20but%20trouble%20for%20me.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_19%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Micaiah%20continued%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BListen%20to%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20says!%20I%20saw%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20sitting%20on%20his%20throne%20with%20all%20the%20armies%20of%20heaven%20around%20him%2C%20on%20his%20right%20and%20on%20his%20left.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_20%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20said%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BWho%20can%20entice%20Ahab%20to%20go%20into%20battle%20against%20Ramoth-gilead%20so%20he%20can%20be%20killed%3F%26%23x2019%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BThere%20were%20many%20suggestions%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_21%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20finally%20a%20spirit%20approached%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20said%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BI%20can%20do%20it!%26%23x2019%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_22%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3B%26%23x2018%3BHow%20will%20you%20do%20this%3F%26%23x2019%3B%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BAnd%20the%20spirit%20replied%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BI%20will%20go%20out%20and%20inspire%20all%20of%20Ahab%26%23x2019%3Bs%20prophets%20to%20speak%20lies.%26%23x2019%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3B%26%23x2018%3BYou%20will%20succeed%2C%26%23x2019%3B%20said%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%26%23x2018%3BGo%20ahead%20and%20do%20it.%26%23x2019%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_23%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BSo%20you%20see%2C%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20has%20put%20a%20lying%20spirit%20in%20the%20mouths%20of%20all%20your%20prophets.%20For%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20has%20pronounced%20your%20doom.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_22_24%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%2